headline: Institutional Buyers Revisit Centene As Medicaid ACA Thesis Gains Traction
summary: AQR Capital Management, Oakmark Select Fund, and Greenlight Capital have recently increased their positions in Centene (NYSE:CNC). These investors are building exposure to Centene's Medicaid and Affordable Care Act focused business model. The moves point to growing institutional interest in the company’s margin normalization, cost controls, and long term earnings durability. Centene is a major managed care player in government sponsored health programs, with a core focus on Medicaid and ACA...
